First up today, Kim Masters gathers the feverish chatter in Hollywood surro=
unding Warner Bros. studio chiefs Mike De Luca and Pam Abdy as their first =
full slate of films rolls into theaters. With some expensive flops in the r=
earview and concerns about ballooning film budgets and risky auteur gambles=
, is David Zaslav, a
notorious belt-tightener, getting ready to send them packing?

=C2=A0

Plus, below the fold: Lauren Sherman assesses the latest collections at Her=
m=C3=A8s, McQueen, and Valentino as Fashion Month finally wraps up. Abby Li=
vingston previews this week=E2=80=99s budget vote as Trump and Mike Johnson=
 attempt to win over G.O.P. hardliners. And John
Ourand has a candid chat with NWSL commissioner Jessica Berman about her to=
p priorities as the ascendant league embarks on its 13th season.

Meanwhile, on the pods: Dylan Byers is joined by Zanny Minton Beddoes, edit=
or-in-chief of The Economist, to discuss how a Lufthansa seat-back-pocket s=
taple is reinventing itself for the digital era. On Fashion People, Lauren =
is joined by fashion
journalist Tish Weinstock to relive Paris Fashion Week and consider Simone =
Bellotti=E2=80=99s appointment at Jil Sander. On The Town, Matt Belloni and=
 Pouya Shahbazian explain his =E2=80=9Ctalent-driven=E2=80=9D approach to A=
=2EI. filmmaking. And on The Powers Tha=
t Be, Leigh Ann Caldwell reunites with=
 Peter Hamby to consider whether Democrats will filibuster the Republican s=
pending bill and gamble with
a government shutdown.

